actions.text: Submitted in the Senate, considered, and agreed to without amendment by Voice Vote.
Called up by House as Privileged Matter.
Resolution Agreed to in House by Yea-Nay Vote: 208 - 179 (Record Vote No: 20).

official_title: A concurrent resolution providing for an adjournment of the House from February 6, 1986 or February 7, 1986 to February 18, 1986, and for an adjournment of the Senate from February 6, 1986 or February 7, 1986 to February 17, 1986.

summary.text: Provides for an adjournment of the House of Representatives from February 6 or 7, 1986, until February 18, 1986, and of the Senate from February 6 or 7, 1986, until February 17, 1986.

titles.title: A concurrent resolution providing for an adjournment of the House from February 6, 1986 or February 7, 1986 to February 18, 1986, and for an adjournment of the Senate from February 6, 1986 or February 7, 1986 to February 17, 1986.
